 <xref rid="insr12402-disp-0001" ref-type="disp-formula">1</xref>) are often seen in the literature. Among those, the most important SIR specification is given as follows. Because the total population 
 <italic>N</italic> remains constant over the duration of infection, by dividing both sides of the ordinary differential equations by 
 <italic>N</italic>, the rates of change in terms of population proportions can be derived, without changing the interpretation of 
 <italic>β</italic> and 
 <italic>γ</italic>. That is, 
