 <italic>et al.</italic>, 
 <xref rid="insr12402-bib-0094" ref-type="ref">2020</xref>). A clear advantage of this alternative form of the SIR model (
 <xref rid="insr12402-disp-0002" ref-type="disp-formula">2</xref>) is that all quantities in the model are adjusted by the population size (which may be allowed to vary in this model formulation), so results obtained from the analyses of data from multiple populations with the SIR model are comparable.
